msgid "The Core Principles of Domain-Driven Design"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
msgid "Ubiquitous Language"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
msgid "One of Jeremy's favorite aspects of DDD is the emphasis on **ubiquitous language** - a shared vocabulary between developers and business stakeholders. He illustrated this with the restaurant industry example: \"86 ketchup\" means \"we're out of ketchup\" to anyone who's worked in restaurants, but is completely nonsensical to outsiders."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
msgid "Since every industry has its own language, DDD encourages teams to:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
msgid "Identify and document domain-specific terminology"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
msgid "Use that language consistently in code, conversations, and documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
msgid "Refine the language iteratively with each sprint or development cycle"
msgstr ""

